article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 59, Stephen F. Austin 52
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jeromie Hill scored 16 points and UTSA hit 7 of 13 3-point attempts en route to a 59-52 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Saturday. Melvin Johnson III added 10 points for the Roadrunners (10-7, 3-1 Southland), who shot 45 percent overall from the field. Jereal Scott had 16 points and Taylor Smith 10 for Stephen F. Austin (9-8, 3-1), which had its four-game winning streak snapped. UTSA led 29-21 at halftime and scored the first seven points of the second half -- five coming from Hill -- to take its biggest lead of the game. The Lumberjacks pulled within 53-49 on a dunk by Hal Bateman with 2:40 remaining, but UTSA's Sei Paye answered with a 3-pointer that banked in as the shot clock expired, and the Roadrunners held on from there. Stephen F. Austin was just 2 for 13 on 3-point attempts while shooting 44 percent overall.
